On Wed, Nov 12, 2003 at 08:54:37AM -0600, Thomas J. Tarka wrote:
> > How many shims did you have installed when you checked end float? You should
> > have had TWO. 
> 
> I thought you always wanted three shims?
> 
> Or do you use two for freshly built engines?

Scott is talking about the procedure for determining what shims are
needed. if you put 2 in then measure endplay, you will get a number.
subtract the endplay desired from that number and put the third shim
of the subtracted thickness in and voila. correct endplay.

